  "text": "While there are cases in which NMFLS and NMFJK outperform the SVD, when the computations are repeated over 10 trials and the results are averaged, as shown in table 5.10, the superiority of NMFLS and NMFJK seems to be vanished. This can be understood since NMF algorithms when converged, only stationarity of the limit points are guaranteed (so not even local-optimality is guaranteed by NMF algorithms). On the other hand, SVD algorithms not only have global-optimality guarantee, but also produce the same factors with differences only in the numerical precision [CITATION_1] (at least theoretically).",
